</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">misc</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">device</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">IOCTL</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">not</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">recognised</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">31744</span>\n<span class=\"n\">misc</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rust</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">misc</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">device</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Exiting</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">the</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Rust</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Misc</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Device</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Sample</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>The order of the device name and module name seems reversed; the C language version of dev_info places the module name first and the device name second.</p>",
