    {
        "content": "<p>I don't have any experience with Rust macros; I'm still struggling to understand how dev_printk is implemented. Could you help fix this?</p>",
        "id": 565790165,
        "sender_full_name": "Zhang Tianci",
        "timestamp": 1767102217
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Actually I don't think you're right.</p>",
        "id": 565790476,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1767102404
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Rust And C both just call <code>_dev_printk</code>, and adding the mod/device name prefix is done inside <code>_dev_printk</code> on the C side.</p>",
        "id": 565790507,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1767102424
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The test results for virtio_device on my module (based on kernel 5.15) are as follows. I'll re-test it on the newest kernel version.</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">hpvs_proxy</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">virtio0</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">read</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">tag</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">PF</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"mi\">0100340082</span><span class=\"n\">f1da5d</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 565790989,
        "sender_full_name": "Zhang Tianci",
        "timestamp": 1767102745
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I added <code>dev_info(&amp;vdev-&gt;dev, \"is creating virtqueue[%u]\\n\", index);</code> in <code>vring_create_virtqueue()</code>, and get these dmesg:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">virtio_blk</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">virtio2</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">is</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">creating</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">virtqueue</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">]</span>\n<span class=\"n\">virtio_blk</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">virtio2</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">is</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">creating</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">virtqueue</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"p\">]</span>\n<span class=\"n\">virtio_blk</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">virtio2</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">is</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">creating</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">virtqueue</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"p\">]</span>\n<span class=\"n\">virtio_blk</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">virtio2</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">is</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">creating</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">virtqueue</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"mi\">3</span><span class=\"p\">]</span>\n<span class=\"n\">virtio_blk</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">virtio2</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">is</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">creating</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">virtqueue</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"mi\">4</span><span class=\"p\">]</span>\n<span class=\"n\">virtio_blk</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">virtio2</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">is</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">creating</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">virtqueue</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"mi\">5</span><span class=\"p\">]</span>\n<span class=\"n\">virtio_net</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">virtio0</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">is</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">creating</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">virtqueue</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">]</span>\n<span class=\"n\">virtio_blk</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">virtio2</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">is</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">creating</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">virtqueue</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"mi\">6</span><span class=\"p\">]</span>\n<span class=\"n\">virtio_net</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">virtio0</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">is</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">creating</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">virtqueue</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"p\">]</span>\n<span class=\"n\">virtio_blk</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">virtio2</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">is</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">creating</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">virtqueue</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"mi\">7</span><span class=\"p\">]</span>\n<span class=\"n\">virtio_net</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">virtio0</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">is</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">creating</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">virtqueue</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"p\">]</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Actually the kmod name is virtio_device's owner rather than virtio_ring. Just like my test above</p>",
        "id": 565792877,
        "sender_full_name": "Zhang Tianci",
        "timestamp": 1767103732
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Oh, I get why! I just misunderstood.</p>\n<p>The print in rust_misc_device is also &lt;device owner + device name:&gt;<br>\n<code>misc</code> is the device owner name, and <code>rust-misc-device</code> is the device name rather than the kmod name. dev_info!() does not print the current kmod name.</p>\n<p>Thanks~</p>",
        "id": 565794073,
        "sender_full_name": "Zhang Tianci",
        "timestamp": 1767104541
    },
